y to the Google Ads or Meta Ads platforms in that advertisers bid in an ad auction to land their business on eligible targeted placements.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-example.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - example ad on bing serp\" width=\"807\" height=\"513\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94779 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-example.webp 807w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-example-480x305.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 807px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>An example Microsoft Ad.<\/em><\/p>\n<p><strong><span data-contrast=\"auto\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" class=\"TextRun SCXW75854542 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW75854542 BCX0\"><span data-contrast=\"auto\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" class=\"TextRun SCXW149649731 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW149649731 BCX0\">\u26a1 <\/span><\/span>Boost your advertising strategy fast <\/span><\/span><\/strong><span data-contrast=\"auto\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" class=\"TextRun SCXW75854542 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW75854542 BCX0\">with our free <a href=\"https:\/\/marketing.localiq.com\/WSLIQContentDLWebsiteAllStarPlaybook.html?cid=Web_Blog_InContent_TextLink_AllStarPlaybook_Download\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">all-star advertising playbook<\/a>!<\/span><\/span><span class=\"EOP SCXW75854542 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{&quot;335551550&quot;:1,&quot;335551620&quot;:1}\">\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<div id=\"microsoft-ads-stats\"><\/div>\n<h2>Need-to-know Microsoft Ads statistics and facts<\/h2>\n<p>Wondering why Microsoft Ads are so important to your business\u2019s ad strategy? Here\u2019s the data you need to know:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Microsoft Bing is the\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/www.reliablesoft.net\/top-10-search-engines-in-the-world\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">second-<\/a>largest\u00a0search engine in the world.<\/li>\n<li>Microsoft Ads have a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.warroominc.com\/institute-library\/blog\/bing-ads-vs-google-ads\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">45%<\/a> higher click-through rate than Google Ads.<\/li>\n<li>Microsoft Ads costs per click and lead can be <a href=\"https:\/\/www.conversios.io\/blog\/microsoft-ads-vs-google-ads-2025\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">30-70%<\/a> lower than the averages in Google Ads.<\/li>\n<li>Microsoft Ads typically returns <a href=\"https:\/\/www.conversios.io\/blog\/microsoft-ads-vs-google-ads-2025\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">$4 to $10<\/a> for every $1 spent.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-stats.jpg\" alt=\"microsoft ads - stats callout\" width=\"897\" height=\"689\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94800 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-stats.jpg 897w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-stats-480x369.jpg 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 897px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<div id=\"microsoft-ads-benefits\"><\/div>\n<h2>Benefits of Microsoft Ads<\/h2>\n<p>Here are a few more Microsoft Ads benefits to consider.<\/p>\n<h3>Microsoft Ads can be more clickable<\/h3>\n<p>On top of the benefits highlighted in the stats above, Microsoft Ads look a bit more like organic results on <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/advertise-on-bing\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bing SERPs<\/a>. Aside from the small \u201cSponsored\u201d text in the ad shown below, you can\u2019t really tell it\u2019s a paid result, which makes users more inclined to click.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-on-serp.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - example ad\" width=\"791\" height=\"512\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94778 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-on-serp.webp 791w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-on-serp-480x311.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 791px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>The Microsoft Ads import tool makes account buildout a breeze<\/h3>\n<p>You can also easily <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/replicate-google-ads-on-bing\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">copy campaigns you\u2019re already running<\/a> on Google Ads or Meta Ads into Microsoft Ads. This simplifies cross-platform advertising management, making Microsoft Ads a no-brainer if you\u2019re already running ads elsewhere.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-auto-import.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - autoimport\" width=\"422\" height=\"600\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94776 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-auto-import.webp 422w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-auto-import-211x300.webp 211w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 422px) 100vw, 422px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong><span data-contrast=\"auto\" xml:lang=\"EN-US\" lang=\"EN-US\" class=\"TextRun SCXW136394741 BCX0\"><span class=\"NormalTextRun SCXW136394741 BCX0\">\ud83d\udea8<\/span><\/span><span class=\"EOP SCXW136394741 BCX0\" data-ccp-props=\"{}\"> <\/span>Are your Google Ads ready to be imported into Microsoft Ads<\/strong>? Find out with an instant account report using our<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> Free Google Ads Grader<\/a>!<\/p>\n<h3>You\u2019re tapping into additional audiences<\/h3>\n<p>One last benefit of Microsoft Ads businesses often forget is that they allow you to tap into audiences you otherwise wouldn\u2019t have been able to reach. Not all consumers are loyal to just one search engine or app, so it\u2019s best to advertise on as many platforms as possible to ensure you\u2019re hitting your target audience at every possible touchpoint.<\/p>\n<div id=\"microsoft-ads-get-started\"><\/div>\n<h2>How to get started with Microsoft Ads<\/h2>\n<p>Follow these five steps to get your business up and running on Microsoft Ads.<\/p>\n<h3>1. Create a Microsoft Ads account<\/h3>\n<p><strong>Navigate <\/strong>to <a href=\"https:\/\/ads.microsoft.com\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ads.microsoft.com<\/a> and click either of the \u201c<strong>Sign up now<\/strong>\u201d prompts.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-homepage.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - homepage screenshot\" width=\"900\" height=\"446\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94782 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-homepage.webp 900w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-homepage-480x238.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>From there, you\u2019ll follow the steps to <strong>input your business information<\/strong>, and you\u2019ll be prompted to import any Meta or Google Ads campaigns you\u2019re running that you want to carry over into Microsoft Ads.<\/p>\n<h3>2. Set your payment method (and know your budget)<\/h3>\n<p>Microsoft Ads will then prompt you <strong>to choose how you want to be billed <\/strong>for any clicks (or other interactions, depending on your ad type) on your ads. You\u2019ll want a reliable payment method here, as an invalid payment will stop your ads from running.<\/p>\n<p>At this point, you\u2019ll likely want to start considering <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/google-ads-budget\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how much you\u2019ll spend on Microsoft Ads<\/a>. This<a href=\"https:\/\/docs.google.com\/spreadsheets\/d\/1o56o0sTJrM5VYBLYclldYqpO1xlBeigHGaup-OAd10A\/copy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> free Microsoft Ads budget template<\/a> can help you navigate this important part of your strategy planning.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-budget-template.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - budget template screenshot\" width=\"900\" height=\"559\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94786 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-budget-template.webp 900w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-budget-template-480x298.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/docs.google.com\/spreadsheets\/d\/1o56o0sTJrM5VYBLYclldYqpO1xlBeigHGaup-OAd10A\/copy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Get the template here<\/em><\/a><em>.<\/em><\/p>\n<h3>3. Create your first campaign<\/h3>\n<p>Once your account is set up, it\u2019s time to start building your Microsoft Ads! Note that if you select to<strong> create an account and campaign<\/strong> (rather than just an account), you\u2019ll be prompted to automatically <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/07\/05\/performance-max-tips\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">create a Performance Max (PMax) campaign<\/a> in Microsoft Ads during the set-up process. You can read up on the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/04\/20\/performance-max-pros-cons\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">pros and cons of PMax<\/a> here.<\/p>\n<h3>4. Review and launch your campaign<\/h3>\n<p>By the step, you\u2019ll want a good understanding of what campaign goals you\u2019re looking to achieve, what audience you\u2019ll want to target, and which ad types you\u2019ll want to create and publish. The tips in this <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/google-ads-account-structure\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Google Ads account structure guide<\/a> can be applicable here, since the two platforms function so similarly.<\/p>\n<p>Basically, once your account is created, you\u2019re able to really dig into your <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/paid-search-strategy\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Microsoft Ads strategy<\/a>. You might want to<strong> hold off on publishing a campaign right away <\/strong>once you get your account sorted, so that you can <strong>ensure your <\/strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/customize-google-ads-conversion-tracking\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>conversion tracking<\/strong><\/a><strong> is set<\/strong> and that you\u2019re confident in the ad setup you\u2019re selecting.<\/p>\n<h3>5. Measure and optimize your Microsoft Ads<\/h3>\n<p>Congratulations! Your business is now up and running on Microsoft Ads. Now, all that\u2019s left to do is <strong>track your campaign performance<\/strong> and <strong>make optimization tweaks <\/strong>as you go.<\/p>\n<p>Read on to the following Microsoft Ads tips for what to do to optimize your ads, and you can jump into the<strong> reporting <\/strong>section of the platform to start measuring your campaign results. If you don\u2019t have a ton of historical data coming in right away to gauge your baseline performance, you can <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/2025-google-ads-benchmarks\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">use industry benchmarks<\/a> to see how you\u2019re doing compared to averages in your industry.<\/p>\n<p>Keep in mind that it might be helpful to lean into third-party tools or marketing partners to analyze your campaign performance, too.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-reporting.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - reporting screenshot\" width=\"900\" height=\"375\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94785 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-reporting.webp 900w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-reporting-480x200.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<div id=\"microsoft-ads-tips\"><\/div>\n<h2>Microsoft Ad tips<\/h2>\n<p>Here are some quick tips for running Microsoft Ads.<\/p>\n<h3>1. Use pre-qualifying terms in your ad copy<\/h3>\n<p>It\u2019s important to keep in mind that the goal of your Microsoft Ads won\u2019t always be to get more clicks. In most cases, the goal is to convert people into paying customers.<\/p>\n<p>For example, if you use controversial or provocative words in your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/01\/03\/ad-copy-examples\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ad copy<\/a> (that aren\u2019t related to your business), you\u2019ll certainly get more clicks on your ads. But how many of those people will turn into your customers? Most likely not too many.<\/p>\n<p>Since you don\u2019t want to waste your advertising budget on useless clicks, it\u2019s a good idea to pre-qualify prospects in your ads to ensure you get targeted traffic.<\/p>\n<p>If you look at the image below, there\u2019s no confusion about who the ad is for. The ad doesn\u2019t try to target all dog food buyers. It explicitly states \u201cbest dog food for picky dogs\u201d in the headline to specifically target people looking for the best dog food for their dog with selective taste buds. So, you can be quite confident that most people who click the ad likely fit that description.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-example-ad.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - example microsoft ads copy\" width=\"900\" height=\"536\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94784 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-example-ad.webp 900w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-example-ad-480x286.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>2. Leverage ad extensions<\/h3>\n<p>Ad extensions in Microsoft Ads function similarly to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/google-ads-assets\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">ad assets in Google Ads<\/a>. These are additional links, buttons, and bits of information you can tack onto your ads to make them larger, more eye-catching, and actionable.<\/p>\n<p>For instance, it\u2019s no secret that a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/04\/13\/call-to-action-examples\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">strong call to action (CTA)<\/a> prompts people to take action.<\/p>\n<p>You can include a CTA button in your Microsoft ads using an action extension. The action extension displays a CTA button next to your ad\u2019s description, making it easy for people to spot and click.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-extensions.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - extensions\" width=\"900\" height=\"605\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94787 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-extensions.webp 900w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-extensions-480x323.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>\ud83d\udcda\u00a0<strong>Free guide download<\/strong>\u00a0&gt;&gt;\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/marketing.wordstream.com\/WSLIQContentDLWebsite36CallToActionPhrases.html?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_36CallToActionPhrases_Download\">The 42 Best Call to Action Phrases Ever (&amp; Why They Work)<\/a><\/p>\n<h3>3. Leverage social proof<\/h3>\n<p>Many of us naturally turn to others to help us decide when we have limited information about certain products or services.<\/p>\n<p>If there\u2019s strong evidence that other people find what you sell valuable, that will often serve as enough catalyst to convert people.<\/p>\n<p>While it\u2019s difficult to provide convincing enough <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/social-proof\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">social proof<\/a> in your search ad where there\u2019s limited space, you can still include some social proof in your ad using a review extension. The extension allows you to display a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/how-online-reviews-impact-your-business\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">positive review<\/a> from your existing customer.<\/p>\n<p>Alternatively, you can simply add a social proof element to your ad text or images. For instance, the example Microsoft Audience Network image ad below shows how the company tries to communicate credibility in its creative and copy.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-display-ad.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - audience network ad example\" width=\"599\" height=\"606\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94777 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-display-ad.webp 599w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-display-ad-480x486.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 599px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>4. Be specific with your offers<\/h3>\n<p>Your Microsoft Ads should clearly showcase what they offer. For instance, if your business offers a discount, you want to communicate exactly how much discount the customer is getting rather than writing vague statements, such as \u201chuge discounts.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>You only get limited space on Bing results pages, and it takes less than a few seconds for customers to decide if they will bother with your ads. So, make sure you display the most enticing offer that\u2019ll grab their attention.<\/p>\n<h3>5. Try a variety of campaigns and ad types<\/h3>\n<p>Microsoft Ads has expanded just as much as other major advertising platforms over the last few years. Now, advertisers have more options than ever to expand their reach and constantly serve up fresh ads to their audiences. Take advantage of as many different campaigns and ad types in Microsoft Ads to ensure you\u2019re tapping into every possible ad placement for your business.<\/p>\n<p>Your Microsoft Ads campaign options are as follows:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Search<\/li>\n<li>Shopping<\/li>\n<li>Streaming<\/li>\n<li>Lodging (for hotels and hospitality businesses)<\/li>\n<li>Performance Max<\/li>\n<li>Audience<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>All six of these campaign types allow for different ad formats, like <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/04\/05\/responsive-search-ad-copy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Responsive Search Ads<\/a>, image and <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/video-marketing-for-small-business\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">video ads<\/a>, and so on.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-campaign-menu.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - campaign options\" width=\"900\" height=\"546\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94783 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-campaign-menu.webp 900w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-campaign-menu-480x291.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>6. Leverage automation when you can<\/h3>\n<p>Similar to Google or Meta Ads, Microsoft Ads offers <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ai-experiments\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">AI capabilities<\/a> directly within the platform to streamline your ad workflows. For example, you can use Microsoft\u2019s <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2023\/06\/05\/generative-ai-in-digital-marketing\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">generative AI options<\/a> to create, edit, or expand images for your ads.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-ai.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - ai image example\" width=\"900\" height=\"338\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94780 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-ai.webp 900w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-ai-480x180.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>In your campaign settings, you can have <a href=\"https:\/\/localiq.com\/blog\/google-ads-ai-copy-tool\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">auto-generated assets<\/a> created for your ad headlines and descriptions, too.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-campaign-settings.webp\" alt=\"microsoft ads - campaign settings screenshot\" width=\"900\" height=\"203\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-94781 size-full\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-campaign-settings.webp 900w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/10\/microsoft-ads-campaign-settings-480x108.webp 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 900px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Additionally, Microsoft Ads has fully <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2023\/01\/23\/optimize-performance-max-campaigns\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">automated campaign types, like Performance Max<\/a>, if you\u2019re unsure of where to start or don\u2019t have a ton of time to oversee a campaign.<\/p>\n<p>At minimum, you\u2019ll likely find yourself using an <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/google-ads-automated-bidding\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">automated bidding strategy<\/a>, as that\u2019s the standard for most accounts at this point. This is because it\u2019s best for your bids (the most you\u2019re offering to pay for an ad placement or click) to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/google-ads-smart-bidding\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">adjust automatically according to each ad auction<\/a> in real time.<\/p>\n<h2>Turn your Microsoft Ad ideas into reality<\/h2>\n<p>If Microsoft Advertising sounds like a good idea for your business, it\u2019s time to turn that idea into action! Getting set up on Microsoft Ads is quick and easy, and with this powerful platform, you can turn your leads and sales dreams into reality. For more ways to maximize your Microsoft Ads success, see how <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/marketing-services?cid=Web_WS_InContent_Demo_Blog_Demo\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">our solutions<\/a> can help!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>See how Microsoft Ads can benefit your business, and find out how you get started, in this full walk-through. <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":69,"featured_media":94794,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"_et_pb_use_builder":"","_et_pb_old_content":"","_et_gb_content_width":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[5],"tags":[],"dipi_cpt_category":[],"class_list":["post-94774","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-paid-search-marketing"],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optim